{
  "key": "SM-1049",
  "fields": {
    "summary": "Certificate Module - Set up a Oops page if user accesses the log in screen ",
    "description": {
      "type": "doc",
      "version": 1,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "\ud83d\udcdd User Story: Display Oops Page When Accessing Certificate Module Login Screen"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "As A: User of the Certificate Manager module"
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "I Want To: Be shown a clear \"Oops\" error page if I access the login screen directly or via an invalid/corrupted URL"
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "So That: I am not confused by unexpected redirects and receive a clear message that the page or action is not available."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Acceptance Criteria (ACs)"
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "AC1: If a user navigates directly to the Certificate Manager login screen (e.g., by stripping the UID from the URL or using an invalid certificate link), the system must display a user-friendly \"Oops\" error page."
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "AC2: The \"Oops\" page must clearly state that the requested page or action is unavailable or invalid."
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "AC3: The \"Oops\" page must provide a way for the user to navigate back to a safe location (e.g., dashboard or home page)."
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "AC4: The system must not redirect users to a blank or broken page in these scenarios."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Scenario Example"
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Input: User navigates to "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "https://sitemanager.betacom.com/app/webroot/cmdist/#/",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "attrs": {
                    "href": "https://sitemanager.betacom.com/app/webroot/cmdist/#/"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " (with no valid certificate UID)"
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Expected Output: The user sees an \"Oops\" error page explaining the issue and offering navigation options."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Original Description:"
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "if in the CERT manager, they get to the login screen, it automatically redirect them to an oops page. I was here ("
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "https://sitemanager.betacom.com/app/webroot/cmdist/#/public-certificate/16812)",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "attrs": {
                    "href": "https://sitemanager.betacom.com/app/webroot/cmdist/#/public-certificate/16812)"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "("
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "https://sitemanager.betacom.com/app/webroot/cmdist/#/public-certificate/16812",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "attrs": {
                    "href": "https://sitemanager.betacom.com/app/webroot/cmdist/#/public-certificate/16812"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "))  and then just sripped off the UID till I got something ("
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "https://sitemanager.betacom.com/app/webroot/cmdist/#/)",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "attrs": {
                    "href": "https://sitemanager.betacom.com/app/webroot/cmdist/#/)"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "("
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "https://sitemanager.betacom.com/app/webroot/cmdist/#/",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "attrs": {
                    "href": "https://sitemanager.betacom.com/app/webroot/cmdist/#/"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "))"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
